         <abstract>
            <p>If a, b and n are positive integers with b ≥ a and n ≥ 3, then the equation of the title possesses at most one solution in positive integers x and y, with the possible exceptions of (a, b, n) satisfying b = a + 1, 2 ≤ a ≤ min{0.3n, 83} and 17 ≤ n ≤ 347. The proof of this result relies on a variety of diophantine approximation techniques including those of rational approximation to hypergeometric functions, the theory of linear forms in logarithms and recent computational methods related to lattice-basis reduction. Additionally, we compare and contrast a number of these last mentioned techniques.</p>
          </abstract>
